Known bugs:

 - FIXME_TODO.bovex
 - you can have the same field twice in an object literal; this
   should not be allowed.

Code health:

 - Add tests for standard library in bovex itself.
 - Documentation (bovex.txt)

Make document look better:
 - actual boxes-and-glue (vertical)
 - bibliography in order
 - pack columns vertically using pack-boxes

Features:

 - It turns out to be very useful to be able to split out expensive
   animations into their own documents that are rendered independently.
   It would be nice if these were just part of the same bovex file
   but could be rendered or re-rendered using a command-line flag.

Fixes and missing stuff:

 - whole-doc optimization loop exists but it is not integrated

 - xrefs

 - When choosing the next split point for rephrase, we can also include
   the badness up to that point (if we can run get-boxes and pack-boxes
   with the same parameters). Although this is not guaranteed to
   lead to a good overall paragraph, it is probably a very good heuristic.

 - tweak expansion/contraction penalties after commas, periods,
   semicolons, colons (and other).

 - bug: comments actually induce whitespace beginning paragraphs, or
   blank spaces between paragraphs. This should be fixable now with
   symbolic bytecode.

 - tweak break penalty at end of text (orphans)

 - column layout allowing for headers, footers

 - Could rephrase a single sentence at a time, providing the context
   of the paragraph in the prompt. This would probably be a lot more
   practical, in several ways.

 - option to include hyphens within the line (I think it looks good
   with them hanging out, but it's probably a bug that it happens)


Minor improvements:
 - Implement pretty-printing lib and use that for output of
   expressions and types

 - Better handling of leading space in getboxes (or call to getboxes).

Expansive ideas:

 - could compile the whole paper (inference and all) to postscript??
